#Text=I should actually apologize slightly if there ’s much overlap between these questions and questions you got during the panel .
#Text=R.
#Text=When I ’ve done this so much I have no memory of past questions .
#Text=You can ask me the same thing three or four times .
#Text=Maybe I should and then go back to the same question later and see .
#Text=So if you had to give advice to someone starting a webcomic
#Text=what would you say ?
#Text=R. Do n’t look at xkcd and think that it means that you do n’t have to take care with what you do .
#Text=There are a lot of comics that have the same general idea , good writers , but they do n’t realize that presentation is important .
#Text=Just because a comic is successful with stick figures does n’t mean you can make it hard to read ; that you should scan it sloppily .
#Text=It 's important to think about it from the readers looking at it , and see from their point of view , like are they going to get it .

#Text=Another big tumbling block is do not comment on your jokes after you make them , do not write “ this is how I feel about this comic ” because then they wo n't form their own opinions and they wo n’t believe the ones they ’ve formed .
#Text=Pay a lot of attention to the experience of someone reading it , and keep that in mind .

#Text=I know just from reading the forums on xkcd that some people have been critical as it ’s become more of a standardized joke-a-day webcomic instead of a personalized more or less scans of your old pages and artwork .
#Text=How would you respond to that ?
#Text=RM .

#Text=I guess only about 2 % of the population is going to like the strip in the first place so I always expected that there are a lot of people who do n’t like the strip and are n’t going to read it .
#Text=Frequently people started reading for the more artistic stuff and then now want more of that .
#Text=I do n’t really know what to say to that other than that what I ’m doing is what I feel like I have to contribute more of .
#Text=I feel like there are a lot of people who are good at the kind of art they are doing and you know , have better messages there .
#Text=Whereas when I ’m telling a joke and I get it just right
#Text=that ’s what I ’m doing well .
#Text=I ’m just just doing whatever I think I can do well and will be proud of and so if that wanders from one thing to another over time , that ’s not something I can control .
